<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB04939</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT EXEMPTING  PHILIPPINE SEA SALT FROM MANDATORY IODIZATION, AMENDING FOR THE PURPOSE REPUBLIC ACT NO. 8172, OTHERWISE KNOWN AS AN ACT FOR SALT IODIZATION NATIONWIDE (ASIN), AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Seeks to exempt natural sea salt from mandatory iodization since the law has effectively discouraged its sale, thereby inhibiting the development of local sea salt farming; Aims to promote salt iodization as an effective strategy for the prevention and control of iodine deficiency disorders and to ensure that small-scale and subsistence producers are not adversely affected.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>SALO, RON P., LACSON, VIRGILIO S.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2017-02-01</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Lanete (074 2017-02-22)</td><td>2. Calalang (000 2018-01-23)</td><tr><td>3. Hernandez (P.) (000 2018-12-18)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON HEALTH ON 2017-02-08</td></tr></table>